In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki discussed President Biden's trip to La Crosse, Wisconsin, where he will promote the Bipartisan Infrastructure Framework. Psaki highlighted specific Wisconsin issues that the infrastructure plan will address, such as replacing lead water service lines and expanding broadband access. She also mentioned that the President and First Lady will be traveling to Surfside, Florida, to meet with first responders and families affected by the building collapse. Psaki provided updates on vaccine shipments to Bangladesh and ongoing outreach efforts to Congress, particularly to progressives, regarding the infrastructure package. She addressed concerns about the situation in Afghanistan and Tucker Carlson's claim that the NSA is spying on him. Psaki also mentioned the House passing bipartisan bills related to science and R&D and the ongoing discussions about the reconciliation package.